                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3d50gh5c/manifest/annotation/p4",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p><hi rend=\"underline\">Daily Advertiser</hi> I send you a copy of\n                                        the<lb/> appeal made to the public by the Committee<lb/> who\n                                        have taken the matter in hand. To<lb/> save postage I have\n                                        enclosed the same<lb/> in a small package of my papers to\n                                        your<lb/> address. Perhaps you may notice the<lb/> matter in\n                                        the <hi rend=\"underline\">Occident</hi>. I may here\n                                        after<lb/> give you some account of a reform I<lb/> am\n                                        trying to introduce at our adjunto<lb/> (the English &amp;\n                                        German <sic>shool</sic>) I mean a<lb/> reform in the <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">Constitution of the Vestry</hi><lb/>\n                                        <hi rend=\"underline\">not in the mode of worship</hi></p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><persName>Mr <add>?</add></persName> has this\n                                        moment left<lb/> me. He desires me to convey his\n                                        regards<lb/> so does <persName>Mr Peixotto</persName>,\n                                                  <persName>Miss P</persName> and all<lb/> the\n                                        family</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(3)\">I am Dear Sir</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(4)\">Respectfully yours</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(4)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">Isaac <add>?</add></persName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p><persName>Miss Peixotto</persName> begs that you<lb/> will be good\n                                        enough to com-<lb/>-municate to her friends the demise\n                                        of<lb/> her mother and to say that in consequence<lb/> of\n                                        her affliction she is unable now to write</p>\n                              <div>\n                                        <p>\n                                                  <ref target=\"Occident_PDFs/Occ_8_10.pdf\">The above\n                                                  text refers to Occident Volume 8 No. 10 page 524.\n                                                  Click here to view.</ref>\n                                        </p>\n                              </div>\n                    </body>\n          </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3d50gh5c/canvas/p4"
                }
              ]
            }
